## Project Structure / 项目结构

- `docs/literature/`: papers, source notes, and reading queue.
- `docs/plans/`: research, computation, experiment, milestone, and risk plans.
- `docs/records/`: decisions and task execution logs.
- `code/`: reusable source code, scripts, notebooks, tests, and configuration.
- `raw_data/calculations/<system_slug>/<case_slug>/`: immutable calculation inputs, outputs, pre-relax structures, and post-relax structures grouped by system and case.
- `raw_data/`: immutable source data and explicitly marked intermediate data.
- `formal_data/structures/<system_slug>/`: only user-approved reusable structures.
- `formal_data/`: validated, user-approved, publication-ready artifacts with provenance.

## Data Rule / 数据规则

```text
raw_data -> code processing -> validation -> user approval -> formal_data
```

Read `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` before changing research scope or scientific assumptions.
For VASP projects, define the relax/SCF/band/DOS/phonon parameter envelope in
`docs/plans/computation_plan.md` before production runs and follow
`AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md`: use `vasp-workflow` for running/orchestration,
`vasp-work-manager` for records/archive/verification, and `vasp-analysis` for
completed-output data processing, figures, reports, and recommendations.
The `raw_data/formal_data` lifecycle belongs to this local project. On clusters,
keep outputs and `analysis/` products inside each source case and maintain only
a concise project-level `docs/project_summary.md` index.
